  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, take your chicken out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>ground allspice, ground smoked paprika</strong> and <strong>cayenne pepper </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a plate with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and mix it all together, then add the <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> to the plate and turn them several times until fully coated in all the spices – this is your <strong>coated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1690363722885-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1690363722885-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1690363722885-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1690363722885-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-1690363722885-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated chicken </strong>to the pan and cook for 7-8 min on each side or until charred and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1690363726411-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1690363726411-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1690363726411-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1690363726411-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-1690363726411-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, drain and finely chop your <strong>pineapple</strong>,<strong> </strong>reserve 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> pineapple juice</strong></p><p>Tip: Don’t chuck pineapple juice down the drain. Instead, add it to your smoothies, cakes or marinades!</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>shallot[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>and chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and shred finely/ roughly shred</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-1690363729694-x200.jpg",
